21. Merge Two Sorted Lists

Solution - 
Time Complexity - O(n)
Space Complexity - O(1)

```
# Definition for singly-linked list.
# class ListNode:
#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):
#         self.val = val
#         self.next = next
class Solution:
    def mergeTwoLists(self, list1: Optional[ListNode], list2: Optional[ListNode]) -> Optional[ListNode]:
        dummy = new_head = ListNode(0)
        while list1 and list2: #while both of the list pointers is pointing to some node
            if list1.val <= list2.val:  #here if list1 value is less then we are making our dummy
                dummy.next = list1      #point to that list1 node
                list1 = list1.next      #and moving forward that list1 node
                dummy = dummy.next      #similarly moving the dummy node to its next
            
            else:
                dummy.next = list2
                list2 = list2.next
                dummy = dummy.next
            
        if list1 or list2:              #this ensures attachment of any list1 or list2 if nodes are present
            dummy.next = list1 or list2
        
        return new_head.next
```
